e best things that I have ever come up with. The bases of magic and races comes from the game, &quot;The kingdoms Telgard&quot;. Hope you enjoy it. I'm maybe thinking of turning this into a manga. But i gotta see how many people volunteer first. Enjoy~<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Saladin Gallows (Sal for short) was brought up in a poor, but intelligent, house. He had the blackest of fur that gave a brillant blue sheen. His eyes were a merry grey with gold flecks in them. He was the one that parents of daughters would like them to marry. So to put it blunty, he was a handsome Mishaar!  His parents were merchants who had no problem selling there abundant stock of ales and wines. It was keeping the money that was the hard part! The Gallows, known as the best brewers in the village, could be one of the richest family's in the village. But they're plagued by the Gallows Curse. The tendecy to waste money on outlandish bets. It's a habit that goes back quite a ways. So they don't even fight it any more. They just throw their money on the table, and wish for the best. Which never turns out to be the best at all!<br>
<br>
And besides having the Gallows curse, Saladin also had the &quot;intelligence curse&quot;. He called it that because his speech was much different then the native Misharr toungue. Instead of rolling his r's and hissing alot, he spoke more refined and hissed very little. Because of this he was ridiculed by both peers and elders alike. So he purposely rolls his r's and hisses. And he ends up sounding like an &quot;out-of-towner&quot; trying to fit in with the natives. Not to mention he spits alot.<br>
<br>
When Saladin reaches the tender age of 12, the Gallows Curse takes no time claiming him. He makes the most outrageous bets. Bets like who can run headfirst into a wall the hardest. One such bet (who can keep there tail in a fire the longest) cost him his tail! It was so burnt, it fell right off! He won the bet by the way! <br>
<br>
Now Saladin is poor, &quot;dumb&quot;, and has no tail. Not a winning combination. The local villagers waste no time in letting the Gallow family know it. They call him half breed, meaning he's only half Misharr. Saladin hates bringing all of this negative attention on his family, he has to stop it. So he runs away. <br>
<br>
He decides to go to the Koresh Kingdom. There he hoped to learn sorcery. Now Saladin was told that magic was an evil and dangerous thing. But he figured that only evil people abuse the power and thus, they do evil things. Saladin only wanted to help people. He aslo wanted to grow back his tail, which was the seed of all this. After about a weak of stumbling lost in the forest, Saladin comes across a portly dwarf who was christened Moente'. Mo for short. He was a squat elf with crimson skin and a turned up nose. His ears were large, large even for a dwarf. Both ears held a gold earring that weighted down his ears.  Mo was busy hunting in the forest and almost shot Saladin! Saladin yelled, &quot;aahhhh don't shoot!&quot;<br>
<br>
After eyeing the foreign beast for a while he said ,&quot;A Misharr heh what ye doing all the way out 'ere?&quot;, Mo asked looking skeptical, &quot; And where's ye tail?&quot; he chuckled heartily.<br>
<br>
Many hours later after Saladin finished his tale. Mo says, &quot;Aye, ye got yourself in a predicament all right. Come to my place, we'll have some grub and set out for the next town in the morning&quot;.<br>
<br>
The next morning, Mo and Saladin set out to the kingdom of Korresh. They had to trek through the grasslands and forest of the countryside. But they didn't seem to mind. To pass the time, Saladin asked of Mo's family.<br>
<br>
&quot;So Mo, what brings you to these parts&quot;, asked Saladin, &quot;where's your family?&quot;<br>
<br>
Mo answered blunty, &quot;Don't ave' any family&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh c'mon now, everyone has family&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Not me&quot;.<br>
<br>
Saladin decided to leave it at that because Mo was obviously in a state of longing. He thought he even saw a fat tear escape his eye. Instead of pestering Mo, Saladin occupied himself with the sights. He had never seen trees this big in his home village of Druaknite in the kingdom of Garr. And there were also a variety of plants and animals in the village. They walked steadily on for the whole day. Not once stopping for a break. When the sun had set and was well below the trees, Mo stopped.<br>
<br>
&quot;Time to rest matey, we'll pick it up in the morning&quot;.<br>
<br>
And so they did. It went on like this for four and a half days. On the fourth day, Saladin excitedly pointed out colored flags on the horizon. <br>
<br>
&quot;Is that the place Mo?&quot; questioned Saladin.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, Sal me matey, that be the place alright&quot;, said Mo as a slight smile crept upon his face&quot;. <br>
<br>
They hurridely rushed to the village surrouning the castle and tried to locate an inn. <br>
<br>
&quot;Wow&quot;, says Saladin, &quot;It's so. Big!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Relax. Try not to look like you've never seen alot of people before&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm trying. There's just so many of em! Wahh!!! what's that?&quot; Said Saladin pointing to a goblin.<br>
<br>
The goblin looked there way. &quot;Got something to say punk!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Sorry sir&quot;, said Mo, &quot;Don't mind him. He be nothing but a small town kid&quot;<br>
<br>
The goblin poked Saladin in the chest. &quot;Watch it next time kid, or i'll have ye hide fer brekfist!&quot;<br>
<br>
As the goblin trotted off Mo muttered softly, &quot;Way to go, we've not been in town two whole minutes and already you're stirrin' up trouble. Ye better watch it kid!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Sorry Mo&quot;, Saladin started, &quot;I was-&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;HALT!!&quot; cried a strong voice.<br>
<br>
Mo and Saladin froze<br>
<br>
&quot;Where do you think you two are going?&quot;<br>
<br>
Not realizing it, Mo and Saladin started to wonder into a big colorful building.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sorry&quot;, said Saladin. &quot;We were searching for a place where I could learn the skill of magic&quot;.<br>
<br>
Mo tried to shut him up, but he was too late. Saladin had already uttered the &quot;M&quot; word, Magic. But to his surprise, THe man didn't seem the slighest bit angry. Instead, he looked excited?<br>
<br>
&quot;Ahh!&quot; Exclaimed the man. &quot;Apprentices! Right this way sirs!&quot;<br>
<br>
The man started to walk towards the castle. Mo and Saladin looked at each other and shrugged. They had no choice but to follow him.<br>
<br>
<br>
