<br>
CHAPTER 2<br>
<br>
The man chatted excitedly as he led them through the halls. &quot;This is very exciting for us. It isn't everyday we get apprentices. And especially for magic! In many places that's considered a dark art!<br>
<br>
&quot;Really?&quot; asked Saladin sarcastically.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh yes indeed. People don't like the thought of othes being able to manipulate things. Quite frankly I don't like it either. But magic can be used for good too&quot;, stated the man.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yea that's why i want to learn it&quot;, explained Saladin. &quot;To help people&quot;. <br>
<br>
&quot;What about your tail?, asked Mo mischeviously.<br>
<br>
Saladin looked at Mo sheepishly, &quot;Well that too&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Where are we going anyway?&quot; asked Mo. <br>
<br>
&quot;To your new teacher, Sampetra M. Breeze&quot;, answered the man briskly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Can she fix my tail?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh I wouldn't know about that, you'll just have to ask her when we get there&quot;.<br>
<br>
As they walked along the winding corridors, Saladin couldn't help but stare at the massive tapestries that hung on the walls. There were pictures of men wearing armor and striking daring poses. And others sages sitting peacefully on a hilltop with dozens people surrounding them. They were pictures of heroes. Dozens of them lined the halls in honorable respect. &quot;My image will grace these halls someday&quot;, promised Saladin to himself.<br>
<br>
&quot;We're heeeere!&quot; announced the man in excitement.<br>
<br>
They stood before a tall wooden double door that was nine feet tall. The door had carved in it a depiction of an ancient battle between all sorts of races. Commonly known as the Race Wars. With a light shove from the man, the double doors opened to reveal a library! But not just any library. THE library. Shelf upon shelf upon shelf upon shelf lined the huge room. and there were multiple floors.<br>
<br>
&quot;Wow&quot;, whispered Saladin and Mo in amazement.<br>
<br>
&quot;Amazing isn't it&quot;, said the man. &quot;It took centuries to gather all these record scrolls. This is the second biggest library in the country.<br>
<br>
In the back a chamber door could be heard opening.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ahh, here she comes&quot;<br>
<br>
