<br>
&quot;just once I'd like to stay for a chance&quot;, muttered Humphrey down the hall. It's always Humphrey go fetch our visitors, nevermind that I may want a cup of tea&quot;.<br>
<br>
Sampetra chuckled,&quot;That man doesn't realize how much I appreciate him. Anyway, on to more pressing bussiness. You both come to learn the skills of magic? Correct?<br>
<br>
&quot;No&quot;, stated Saladin, &quot;just me&quot;.<br>
 <br>
&quot;Are you sure&quot;, asked Sampetra in a knowing tone.<br>
<br>
Saladin looked at Mo. &quot;You want to learn also?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes&quot;, said Mo. &quot;I'd like to learn the properties of the elements and how to manipulate them&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well then, you can certainly learn them under me. But all I ask is one thing.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;what's that!&quot;, asked Mo.<br>
<br>
&quot;You must be willing to learn the bad, along with the good. This will not be easy. I want students who are eager to learn and strive for perfection. Do you think you can do that?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes&quot;, they both answered.<br>
<br>
&quot;Excellent. We start tommorow.&quot;<br>
<br>
Humphrey walked back in the room. &quot;Gentlemen, I shall escort you to your rooms&quot;.<br>
<br>
When they looked back at the spot that Sampetra last stood, there was nothing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well I'll be a minotaurs rump. Where'd she go?&quot;, asked Mo?<br>
<br>
&quot;M'lady has a way of dissapearing on you sometimes&quot;, chuckled Humphrey,&quot;but you never know when she's watching you&quot;, he added with a more serious tone. <br>
<br>
Mo and Saladin looked at each other.<br>
<br>
They arrived at their rooms shortly thereafter, which turned out to be glamourous. It was a circular room with the huge  bed in the middle of the room. Along the stone walls (which were colored a festive orange) huge tapestries hung everywhere. Most of them showed images of the Race Wars.  There was a huge fire burning in the hearth and stew was cooking over it. The room was filled with the aroma of Chicken soup. On the bed were fresh clothes and towels. There was also a note.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Dear Saladin, <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Class begins at 9:00 AM sharp in the<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp library. Be prompt or don't bother<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp showing up!<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp    -Sampetra<br>
<br>
Saladin chuckled and tossed the note aside. What he really wanted to do was tuck into the delicious soup he smelled cooking. He shoveled ladles full of soup into his bowl and sat at the circular table in the corner. Just as he as about to take a sip, there was a knock at his chamber door.<br>
<br>
Muttering to himself he shuffled briskly to the door, &quot;geez, i was just about to eat, why must they alway bother me at meal time? &quot;<br>
<br>
